  "instructions": [
    "Bring a pot of salted water to a boil and cook the dried noodles for about 8 minutes until al dente, then drain and rinse with cold water.",
    "While the noodles cook, whisk together coconut cream, soy sauce, rice vinegar, lime juice, sesame oil, chili garlic sauce, peanut butter, toasted sesame seeds, and a pinch of salt in a small bowl until smooth.",
    "Toss the drained noodles with the sauce, ensuring each strand is coated evenly.",
    "Divide the noodles between two bowls.",
    "Top each bowl with diced cucumber, sliced scallions, and crushed roasted peanuts.",
    "Drizzle a little sesame oil over the top for extra shine.",
    "Garnish with a wedge of lime for a citrusy burst.",
    "Serve immediately, letting diners stir all ingredients before eating."
  ],
